Hi,

After analyzing titanium files, I was able to narrow down the cause of win10 folder not being generated. Please have a look at below code :

File - Titanium\mobilesdk\win32\5.4.0.v20160601151241\windows\templates\module\default\hooks\windows-module.js

Code - function isWindows10() {
				return (os.release().indexOf('10.0') == 0);
	   }

The value of os.release() on my windows 10 system for windows 10 sdk gives value "6.3.2". 

My build command for the module has --wp-sdk 10.0.0 .  When running the application with --wp-sdk 10.0.0 generates win10 folder , but the module does not generate the folder.

Can you please have a look.

Thanks
